This Naf Naf Grill location is moderately well designed for the Chicago lunch rush. They had railings to guide people in a snake like manner all the way up to the food bar. I got there fortunately 2 minutes before the lunch rush. The pita machine was at the very front and flour was scattered everywhere. It was not clean and I was very worried about cross contamination. I ordered a basmati rice bowl with chicken. I think due to the fact that the lunch rush was about to start they skimped on rice. The amount of chicken was the typical small scoop so I did not care much. It was very hard to hear the servers but I pointed and said “I want this”. I asked for lots of pickles and the server put so little, she looked at me if I wanted more and I said to put more on. Then she grabbed a bigger scoop and added it to my bowl and that was the perfect amount. I got red cabbage, onions, tahini sauce, garlic sauce, and hummus. I got to the register and they told me my meal was over $10. I was hungry at the time so I didn’t care that it was over what I expected. Did my research and found out that the hummus is $1.50 extra. I wish someone had told me that before they scooped it on. Upon trying to leave during the lunch rush I struggled because once the railings fill up there is nowhere for people to go, so they all crowd by the door. Over all the food was great tasting and I would return, probably not during the lunch rush.
